<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Non-diatonic substitutions: Eb→Em(vi), A→Am(ii), B major→vi (Em context), C#°→Bm(iii), G7→G(I), F#7→D(V)
- vi (Em) dominates verses — quartal E-B-E LH voicing (two perfect 4ths) throughout
- iii (Bm) = B-F#-B quartal LH — same pattern displaced, gives modal flavor
- vii° (F#°): F#-A-C (diminished triad) used twice as chromatic passing color
- I (G) builds from 3-note (G-D-G) to 4-note (G-D-G-B) by chorus — textural growth
- m4 climax of verse: vi with all 4 LH notes + 3-note RH — peak before half-time feel

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bass line mm. 2-3: E2→B2→C2→G2 — bass voice moves by 4ths/5ths smoothly
- Inner voice m11: iii (B-F#-B) → V (D-A-D-F#) — F# common tone held
- Descending bass line mm. 14, 18: G2→F#2→E2→F#2 — stepwise with passing diminished

TEXTURE ARC:
- Verses mm. 1-8: 3-note LH throughout, 2-note RH — simple and open (vi-modal feel)
- Chorus mm. 9-12: 4-note LH at key points (C-G-C-E, G-D-G-B), 3-note RH at IV
- Peak mm. 13, 17: both I and IV with 4 LH notes, RH reaches G5 then E5
- Final m19: vi with E-B-E-G full 4-note close — ends on minor (characteristic of the carol)
-->
